Policy-based VPN Gateway uses predefined rules (policies) to determine how traffic is encrypted and routed.

It relies on static configurations and does not dynamically adjust routes.

For example, traffic between specific IP ranges is encrypted based on defined policies.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is small organizations with simple network requirements.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is legacy systems that require static VPN configurations.

Policy-based VPNs are easier to configure but less flexible compared to route-based VPNs.
